<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8718] GroovyConsole MacOS fix required for JDK9+</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8718</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per &lt;a href=&quot;http://openjdk.java.net/jeps/272&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://openjdk.java.net/jeps/272&lt;/a&gt;, com.apple.eawt is not supported for JDK9+ and we use that via e.g. MRJPrefsHandler. If I understand correctly, the functionality seems mostly incorporated into java.awt.Desktop.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A common workaround (to maintain JDK8 compatibility and work on JDK9+) seems to be to use reflection to access the new classes, e.g.:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/SubOptimal/keystore-explorer/blob/master/kse/src/org/kse/gui/MacOsIntegration.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/SubOptimal/keystore-explorer/blob/master/kse/src/org/kse/gui/MacOsIntegration.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
